- The White stones at F11, F10, G7, H7, and I7 are part of a group that is surrounded by Black stones.
- The White stone at J9 is surrounded on three sides by Black stones and has only one liberty at J8.

To capture the White stone at J9, Black can play at J8, which will remove the last liberty of the White stone at J9, capturing it.
